==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: clutch hitter
<hw>clutch hitter</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Baseball)</fld> <def>a batter
who hits safely more frequently when men are on base or the team is
behind in the score.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Clutching</qex> at the phantoms of the stock market.</q>
<rj><qau>Bankroft.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clutter</ent>⟦br⟧
